        <TD bgcolor='black' valign='top'><font color='white' face='Verdana' size='2'> As a former guide I can say this.  If you were there first, we will 90% of the time ask the person to move on and find another spot.  The only way we can really bust anyone from training is if we personally see it or there is indisputable evidence of the training.  Indisputable evidence is a report showing a surprisingly large ammount of mobs beating on someone (identified through the report command) for the area in question wiping out the whole group (ie more than one person said it happened, and have the background to prove it).  However to remember we can make ourselves look like we are not even online, and are invisable to everyone reguardless fo see invis spells and could come in to the area and watch you do it.  I would imagine if a verant rep reads this something for the guides/gm's will change and the policy will be updated or something new will be added to a /report command (like the adding of an image file to show the person running at you with a whole bunch of mobs like a screenshot, but held on the server to prevent tampering).  Do it at your own risk, there have been times I was just moving around in game invised and witnessed people intentionally training others and punishment was assigned and the issue was being dealt with even before the player(s) had respawned.  Then again, this was before the /petition change, so guides/GM's were always on the server, rather logged and ready to go where needed.</P><P><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=311916" target="_blank">Lizalfos Deathscale</a><BR></font></td>
